Description: Attack Graph Analysis -- weighted-graph security toolkit
 aga models any network (an IT attack graph, a road system, a supply chain, a
 social/influence graph) as a directed weighted graph and reasons about its
 security and robustness with graph theory:
 .
  * CVSS v3.1 Exploitability-derived edge weights (every weight is traceable to
    a public security standard);
  * a from-scratch Bellman-Ford shortest-path implementation;
  * Menger's Theorem machinery (vertex-disjoint paths + minimum vertex cut,
    solved three independent ways) to find the smallest set of nodes to defend;
  * a composite security score (0-100) with a letter grade (A-F).
 .
 The toolkit also constructs graphs from partial access (with observed-vs-
 inferred provenance) and ingests live WiFi (nmcli/iwlist) and nmap scans.
 .
 It installs the `aga` command. Matplotlib is recommended for rendering graphs;
 live scanning of WiFi/nmap requires explicit --i-am-authorized authorization.
